  "prompt": "Do we connect the output neutral of an inverter to the main neutral line?",
  "response": "Great question! Here's a detailed answer:\n\n1. Grid-Tied Inverters:\n- Should NOT connect the inverter's neutral directly to the main neutral line\n- Requires a separate neutral connection\n- Typically uses a separate neutral bond at the inverter or main panel\n\n2. Off-Grid/Stand-Alone Inverters:\n- May connect neutral depending on specific system design\n- Often have an internal neutral bond\n- Depends on inverter type and manufacturer specifications\n\n3. Best Practices:\n- Always follow manufacturer's installation instructions\n- Consult a licensed electrician\n- Ensure proper grounding and bonding\n- Comply with local electrical codes\n\n4. Potential Issues with Direct Neutral Connection:\n- Can create ground loop problems\n- May cause unwanted current flow\n- Could lead to equipment damage\n\n5. Recommended Approach:\n- Use proper neutral connection methods\n- Ensure electrical safety\n- Get professional installation\n\nAlways prioritize safety and professional guidance when installing electrical systems.",
